# 6. Better Approach (Sliding Window)

## Idea

Maintain a sliding window.

Expand the right pointer.

Whenever window contains

```
a
b
c
```

every larger substring will also be valid.

So,

```
answer += n - right
```

Then shrink from the left.

---

## Algorithm

```
left = 0

for right

    include s[right]

    while window contains all 3

        answer += n-right

        remove left character

        left++
```

---

## Code

```python
class Solution:
    def numberOfSubstrings(self, s: str) -> int:
        freq = {"a": 0, "b": 0, "c": 0}

        left = 0
        ans = 0
        n = len(s)

        for right in range(n):

            freq[s[right]] += 1

            while freq["a"] > 0 and freq["b"] > 0 and freq["c"] > 0:

                ans += n - right

                freq[s[left]] -= 1
                left += 1

        return ans
```

---

## Time Complexity

```
O(n)
```

---

## Space Complexity

```
O(1)
```

---

# 7. Optimal Approach (Last Occurrence Method)

## Intuition

Keep the latest index of

```
a
b
c
```

Suppose

```
Current index = i

Last positions

a = 8
b = 5
c = 10
```

Minimum last position

```
5
```

Every substring ending at `i`

starting from

```
0
1
2
3
4
5
```

contains all three.

Number of choices

```
5 + 1 = 6
```

Hence

```
answer += minimum_last_position + 1
```

---

## Algorithm

```
Store

last_a = -1
last_b = -1
last_c = -1

Traverse string

Update last occurrence

If all exist

    answer += minimum(last positions)+1
```

---

## Code

```python
class Solution:
    def numberOfSubstrings(self, s: str) -> int:
        count = 0
        last = {
            "a": -1,
            "b": -1,
            "c": -1
        }

        for i in range(len(s)):

            last[s[i]] = i

            if last["a"] != -1 and last["b"] != -1 and last["c"] != -1:

                count += min(last.values()) + 1

        return count
```

---

## Dry Run

```
s = "abcabc"
```

| Index | Character | Last (a,b,c) | Minimum | Added | Answer |
| ----- | --------- | ------------ | ------- | ----- | ------ |
| 0     | a         | (0,-1,-1)    | -       | 0     | 0      |
| 1     | b         | (0,1,-1)     | -       | 0     | 0      |
| 2     | c         | (0,1,2)      | 0       | 1     | 1      |
| 3     | a         | (3,1,2)      | 1       | 2     | 3      |
| 4     | b         | (3,4,2)      | 2       | 3     | 6      |
| 5     | c         | (3,4,5)      | 3       | 4     | 10     |

Final Answer

```
10
```

---

## Time Complexity

```
O(n)
```

---

## Space Complexity

```
O(1)
```

