# 9. Why This Works

Suppose

```
Last positions

a = 10

b = 8

c = 15
```

The earliest required character is

```
b at index 8
```

If substring starts after 8,

```
start = 9
```

then

```
b disappears
```

and substring is invalid.

Therefore

Valid starting indices are

```
0
1
2
...
8
```

Total

```
8+1
```

This is exactly

```
min(last positions)+1
```

which counts all valid substrings ending at the current index.

